fr.sii.ogham.core.convert

Class DefaultConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.convert.DelegateConverter
      • fr.sii.ogham.core.convert.DefaultConverter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Converter, ConverterRegistry

    public class DefaultConverter
extends DelegateConverter
    The default converter delegates conversion to registered SupportingConverters. It provides a default conversion behavior:
    • Converts a string separated by , to an array of anything (see StringToArrayConverter). Conversion of each element is applied through the DefaultConverter too
    • Converts a string to a boolean (see StringToBooleanConverter)
    • Converts a string to a number or byte (see StringToNumberConverter)
    If no conversion is required but types differ (sub-class for example), a cast is applied.
